The example in this directory is a simple one image map designed to approximate
a test I reported in the review I wrote for the astrotomography proceedings of
2001.

model.cfg  -- config file to define the model
data.cfg   -- config file defining the data format
data.fits  -- FITS file derived from this using makedata.py then comdat.py
map.cfg    -- config file to define starter map
map.fits   -- FITS file initially generated using makemap.py, updated with
              memit.

To run the example, proceed as follows:

# make the FITS files
makemap.py model model
makedata.py data data
comdat.py model data data -n
makemap.py map map

# now run the mem iterations
memit.py map data 100 2.6 map

# To repeat the test without starting from scratch,
# re-generate the start map, and repeat the final line

makemap.py -c map map
memit.py map data 100 2.6 map


